  "doc_id": "50635",
  "text": "Washed roots can be stored at 4°C for several days before further cleaning and staining procedures start. N-fixing root nodules and ectomycorrhizal roots can be identified visually at lower magnification under a dissecting microscope (see below). Arbuscular and ericoid mycorrhizal fungi inhabit the inside of the roots and the procedures to determine root colonisation by these fungi are more elaborate. Clear and more detailed descriptions of the procedures explained below are given by [CITATION_1] . The species belongs to one of the Categories 1-4 below if the relevant structures are clearly seen in at least a third of the plants, or in at least two plants if only five plants are sampled.",
